metadata.name: Immortal Technicity
metadata.description:
It was a calm afternoon in Iouanacera, renamed Martinique by French settlers. In between lockdowns and social unrest, that stroll through Balata botanic garden felt like a cure and a disease at the same time. Surrounded by a nature so pure, yet so controlled. 

As mosquitoes dined on my blood, I sat down on the nearest bench to scratch a few bites. When I looked back up, it felt as though right on time for a spectacle. The Carbet mountains revealing their timeless beauty behind the curtain. 

Unable to resist loading my camera with a roll infused with purple chemistry, I could not help but wonder : 
"How many apocalypses did they survive? How many more will they witness or shape?" 

Questions left unanswered, I wish I spoke their language. Then I took the shot.
